        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to the models listed above with International I-6 engines. Vehicles operating in
                    severe on-road applications may require the relocation of the Transmission Control Module for better
                    environmental protection. The following procedures are required to relocate the Allison Transmission
                    Control Module from the frame crossmember under the rear of the cab to inside the cab on the cab
                    rear sill on those vehicles equipped with International I-6 engines. TSI-05-13-03 provides the
                    procedures for doing a similar relocation for those vehicles equipped with Caterpillar C10/12 and
                    Cummins ISM engines.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
