        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="6">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes, or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to avoid property damage, personal injury, or death.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the positive and negative battery cables from the battery connectors.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the Transmission Control Module mounted on a bracket to the cab rear mounting
                    cross member. See Figure 1.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0513021" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0513021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Locate Transmission Control Module</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two bolts holding the module bracket to the cross member. The bolts are
                    threaded into weld nuts attached to the inside of the module bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the module cover and disconnect the three harness connectors from the module.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the control module from the mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate (see Figure 1) and disconnect the harness breakouts that are connected to the
                    Road Speed Sensor (rear), the Turbine Sensor (middle - if equipped) and the Engine Speed Sensor
                    (forward - with heat shield) from the right side of the transmission.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the harness from the main transmission connector shown in Figure 1.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">If truck was built on or before June 23, 2002, proceed to step 14.</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If truck was built after June 23, 2002 it will be necessary to add a 5-way connector to
                    the remaining Engine/Trans harness by performing the following steps:
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull harness to the driver's side of the transmission and cut cable per Figure 2.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0613012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0613012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the transmission portion of the harness and discard.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove harness tape wrap towards engine far enough to allow the installation of a 5-way
                    connector. Use connector 3522251C1, terminals 1661875C1 and seals 1661872C1.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Crimp and solder the terminals on the following circuits:</para>
            </step1>
            <table id="t0613012">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.69*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.31*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Cavity</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Circuit</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>L47A157</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>C</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>L92123</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>D</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>L5B183</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>E</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>L5B184</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>Proceed to Step 15.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow the harness above and to the left of the transmission and locate the Engine/Tran
                    5-Way connector and disconnect. See Figure 3.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0513022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0513022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Locate 5 Way Connector</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0513023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0513023.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Locate 24 Way Connector</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow the harness into the engine compartment and locate the Trans/Dash 24-Way
                    connector and disconnect. See Figure 4.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the two body builder connections in the same area as the 24-Way and disconnect
                    (if used). Note their mating connectors. See Figure 4.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the harness breakout above the starter that provides clean power and ground and
                    disconnect it. If this connector has previously been eliminated the splice will have to be cut from
                    the harness and resoldered to the new harness. If the connector has been eliminated, make note of
                    the circuits before disconnecting.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the old harness from the chassis.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lay the new harness on top of the transmission. Figure 5 illustrates the new harness and
                    its connectors.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0613015" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0613015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. New Harness and Connectors</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the transmission connector to the bracket/connector on the right side of the
                    transmission. See Figure 1.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the Vehicle Speed Sensor connector to the Vehicle Speed Sensor at the rear of
                    the transmission. See Figure 1.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the Turbine Speed Sensor (if equipped). See Figure 1.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the Engine Speed Sensor connector to the Engine Speed Sensor at the front of the
                    transmission. See Figure 1.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the Engine/Tran 5-way connector (either to existing connector or the one added
                    in Steps 9-13) on the left side of the engine. See Figure 3.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Route the clean power and ground connector breakout to the connector above the starter
                    motor and connect.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">In the engine compartment, connect the Trans/Dash 24-Way connector and the body builder
                    connectors (Figure 4 - if they were previously connected on the old harness installation).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Route and tie strap the new harness to prevent rubbing, chafing, and/or exposure to
                    extreme temperatures near the exhaust system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Feed the Transmission Control Module connectors and J1939 Resistor through the
                    transmission shift tower opening in the floor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>In some applications the predrilled shift tower cutout may not be available or may be used by
                        other body builder equipment. If necessary drill an additional 2 1/4" hole in the shifter tower
                        filler panel near the existing hole and use rubber grommet to seal the cable and hole.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two weld nuts from the control module mounting bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the mounting bracket at the rear of the cab and use the bracket mounting holes as
                    a template to mark the cab floor above the rear sill for drilling. See Figure 6 for approximate
                    location.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0513025" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0513025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Locate Mounting Holes</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drill two holes appropriate for 3/16" self tapping bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the Transmission Control Module mounting bracket to the two holes drilled in the
                    previous step. Use two 3/16" self tapping bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the three connectors to the Transmission Control Module. Connect the black
                    connector to "Black", the blue connector to "Blue", and the clear connector to "Gray". In addition
                    to being color-coded, all connectors are keyed to fit only the proper module connector; don't force
                    the connector into the wrong mating connector.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the Transmission Control Module to the bracket using the existing hardware.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Seal the cab floor where the cable enters using the old plug and RTV Silicone sealant as
                    required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the battery cables and test for proper operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
